<div id="what-is-mean-total-number-of-steps-taken-per-day" class="section level4">
<h4>What is mean total number of steps taken per day?</h4>
<p>For this part of the assignment, you can ignore the missing values in the dataset.</p>
<ol style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>Make a histogram of the total number of steps taken each day</li>
</ol>
<pre class="r"><code>steps_date &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ date, data=activity, FUN=sum)
str(steps_date)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## 'data.frame':    53 obs. of  2 variables:

<div id="what-is-the-average-daily-activity-pattern" class="section level4">
<h4>What is the average daily activity pattern?</h4>
<ol style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>Make a time series plot (i.e. <code>type = &quot;l&quot;</code>) of the 5-minute interval (x-axis) and the average number of steps taken, averaged across all days (y-axis)</li>
</ol>
<pre class="r"><code>steps_interval &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ interval, data=activity, FUN=mean)
plot(steps_interval, type=&quot;l&quot;)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-5" alt="plot of chunk unnamed-chunk-5" width="672" /></p>
<ol start="2" style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>Which 5-minute interval, on average across all the days in the dataset, contains the maximum number of steps?</li>
</ol>
<pre class="r"><code>steps_interval$interval[which.max(steps_interval$steps)]</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] 835</code></pre>

<h4>Are there differences in activity patterns between weekdays and weekends?</h4>
<ol style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>Create a new factor variable in the dataset with two levels weekday and weekend indicating whether a given date is a weekday or weekend day.</li>
</ol>
<pre class="r"><code>daytype &lt;- function(date) {
    
  if (weekdays(as.Date(date)) %in% c(&quot;Saturday&quot;, &quot;Sunday&quot;)) 
      {&quot;weekend&quot;
       
    } 
    
    else { &quot;weekday&quot;}
    
}
activity$daytype &lt;- as.factor(sapply(activity$date, daytype))</code></pre>
<ol start="2" style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li>Make a panel plot containing a time series plot (i.e. <code>type = &quot;l&quot;</code>) of the 5-minute interval (x-axis) and the average number of steps taken, averaged across all weekday days or weekend days (y-axis).</li>
</ol>
<pre class="r"><code>par(mfrow=c(2,1))
for (type in c(&quot;weekend&quot;, &quot;weekday&quot;)) {
    steps.type &lt;- aggregate(steps ~ interval,
                            data=activity,
                            subset=activity$daytype==type,
                            FUN=mean)
    plot(steps.type, type=&quot;l&quot;,col=&quot;red&quot;, main=type)
}</code></pre>
